{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_63","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: APPROVED\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Checklist\n- [x] `run start` and `run resume` now accept `quick_dev` while preserving the prior snapshot-state preconditions; both handlers pass `project_record.flow` straight into the shared engine in [run.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs#L73) and [run.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs#L153), and the stale rejection path is gone from [error.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs#L10).\n- [x] `quick_dev` still uses the required `plan_and_implement -> review -> apply_fixes -> final_review` order and ignores `prompt_review.enabled`, as defined in [mod.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs#L45) and [mod.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs#L150), with regression coverage in [flow_semantics_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/flow_semantics_test.rs#L94).\n- [x] Start/resume remain canonical-state driven: preflight runs before any mutation in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L224), payload/artifact persistence happens before `stage_completed` in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L1553), and resume reconstructs the next cursor from journal/snapshot state rather than artifacts in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L2163).\n- [x] The shared engine already satisfies the `quick_dev` outcome rules: remediation and `cycle_advanced` on review `request_changes`, failure on review `rejected`, and amendment-backed completion-round restart on late-stage non-approval are handled in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L772), including the amendment-write rollback invariant in [engine.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs#L789).\n- [x] `run status`, `run history`, and `run tail` already read canonical snapshot/journal/artifact state without any flow-specific deferral in [service.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs#L358), and daemon-routed `quick_dev` dispatch goes through the same engine entrypoints in [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L271) and [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L327).\n- [x] Coverage was updated from “quick_dev deferred” to supported behavior: CLI coverage in [cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L2888), engine coverage in [workflow_engine_test.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs#L749), and Gherkin coverage in [run_start_quick_dev.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_quick_dev.feature#L1), [run_resume_non_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_resume_non_standard.feature#L1), and [run_start_standard.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature#L18).\n\n## Notes\nApproval is based on code inspection of commit `4db11a0`. I could not execute the Rust test suite in this environment because `cargo` is not installed, but the implementation matches the loop 12 spec and the added coverage aligns with the newly supported public behavior.\n\n## Commit Message\nenable quick_dev flow for run start and resume"}}
